  "source_id": "ovarian-cancer",
  "name": "Ovarian Cancer - Diagnosis Code Query (Multi-Histology, Female-Specific)",
  "description": "**First female-specific cancer phenotype** (counterpart to male-only Prostate Cancer). Tests ability to find ovarian cancer patients via diagnosis codes by histology: parent ovarian malignancy, primary, neoplasm (broader), serous papillary cystadenocarcinoma (most common epithelial), and endometrioid carcinoma. All patients in expected results are female.",
  "prompt": "Find all female patients with a diagnosis of ovarian cancer, including primary malignancy of ovary, serous papillary cystadenocarcinoma, mucinous cystadenocarcinoma, and endometrioid carcinoma of ovary.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find all patients with ovarian cancer.",
    "broad": "Find all patients diagnosed with ovarian cancer \u2014 including the parent malignant neoplasm of ovary, primary malignant neoplasm of ovary, neoplasm of ovary (broader), serous papillary cystadenocarcinoma (most common epithelial subtype), and endometrioid carcinoma of ovary.",
    "expert": "I need to identify all ovarian cancer patients. Ovarian cancer is documented under multiple SNOMED codes from the ASCO Epithelial Ovarian Cancer VSAC: Malignant neoplasm of ovary (363443007) is the parent, Primary malignant neoplasm of ovary (93934004), Neoplasm of ovary (123843001) \u2014 broader, Serous papillary cystadenocarcinoma ovary (254850005), and Endometrioid carcinoma ovary (254852002). Search Condition resources for all five codes. Note this phenotype is female-only \u2014 male patients should not appear in expected results."
  },
